      <p class="text">
        Bachata is a style of social dance from the Dominican Republic which is
        now danced all over the world.In partnering, the lead can decide whether
        to perform in open, semi-closed or closed position. Dance moves or step
        variety strongly depend on the music (such as the rhythms played by the
        different instruments), setting, mood, and interpretation. Unlike salsa,
        bachata dance does not usually include many turn patterns.
      </p>

